Description:
Spectacular Views And Modern Living In Perfect Location
From Collingwood's prestigious and chic Yorkshire Brewery locale is one of the most excellent examples of city fringe living. This contemporary one-bedroom apartment has all the essentials plus a lot more. Including unobstructed views of the city skyline, and all the way to the Dandenong Ranges from the east-west covered balcony. Features include a stylish modern kitchen with gas cooktop, S/S appliances, stone benches and quality designer cabinetry. Extras include split system air conditioning, tiled bathroom, carpeted bedroom with mirrored robes, secure carpark and storage cage, 'FTTP Broadband', video intercom, double insulation, access to the communal rooftop BBQ and gymnasium. Situated so close to many of the hip bar and cafe treasures, with train and tram options to the city, the Eastern freeway and major arterials.
Insights: 307d/21 Robert Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Classic Victorian, courtyard ambience, prime position
Offering an affordable entry into the enviable inner-city market, this impressive Victorian home has been smartly refurbished offering light-filled living with some special appeal. Benefiting from a side access gate and a stylish interior, the home includes 2 bedrooms, a central living room that opens directly to an undercover side courtyard. Set to the rear is an updated kitchen, stylish bathroom (marble benchtops and over bath shower), and separate laundry along with a deep paved outdoor garden providing the perfect sanctuary to relax and/or entertain in a tranquil environment with plenty of space. Conveniently located only minutes from Smith Street's vibrant cafe scene, schools and freeway access, this inviting home offers a number of positive attributes that will suit owner occupiers & investors alike. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
Insights: 6 Ballarat Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
An opulent conversion: magnificently spacious warehouse style
In the iconic Foy & Gibson precinct, this spectacular heritage residence combines authentic historical detail with an elegant modern aesthetic. Designed for large-scale living and entertaining, and distinguished by soaring ceilings and abundant natural light, here is Melbourne's benchmark for CBD-edge warehouse living. Secluded yet walking distance to vibrant Smith, Brunswick & Gertrude Street cafes and East Melbourne parks. A versatile floor plan incorporates a grandly proportioned living/dining room 4 double bedrooms (or 3 + second study), central study alcove, stylish kitchen opening to garden terrace, and two luxurious bathrooms. Including lift entry from an impressive lobby, two basement car spaces and large storage unit, this stunning property features original timber floors, antique Chinese doors, bespoke storage throughout, heating/cooling and superior appointments.
Insights: 10/115 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018.

Description:
Smith & Co - the ideal lifestyle
With a large north facing balcony overlooking the indigenous central garden, one of several gardens featured in the Smith & Co. development, this immaculately presented apartment with quality fixtures and fittings throughout presents an exceptional opportunity for first homebuyers and astute investors to enter into the increasingly popular inner-north. The apartment comprises a large bedroom with BIRs and study area, expansive and light-filled open plan living and meals with well-appointed kitchen that opens onto the balcony, gleaming central bathroom, Euro laundry, double glazed windows, heating and air-conditioning, secure intercom entry, basement OSP and lift access with direct access to Smith Street. The communal areas of the development feature gardens with covered BBQ areas, rooftop terraces and a library lounge. Enjoying an enviable lifestyle in the heart of bustling Smith Street shopping district and nearby Gertrude and Brunswick Street, you'll find no shortage of popular cafes, bars, fine dining, artisanal boutiques, trams and side-street treasures the area is known for.
Insights: 208/132 Smith Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Great Location! Affordable One Bedroom Apartment!
Oxley Apartment Complex, a development by prominent Melbourne property developer Urban Inc and designed by award winning architects Elenberg Fraser, located in the heart of Collingwood's Foy heritage precinct.
This apartment comes equipped with Stainless steel appliances, double glazed windows, block out roller blinds, bedroom with built-in wardrobes, split system with heating and cooling, open living areas, 1 storage cage (no car space included)
Beyond the apartment, the lush exterior landscapes provide occupants with a secure sanctuary to call home. With plenty of options for entertaining whether it be by the rooftop garden terrace or swimming pool which overlooks Collingwood's decommissioned industrial factories.
Less than 4km from the CBD and even closer proximity to Smith Street bars/cafes/restaurants, Oxley is conveniently located to provide an ideal balance of work and play.

Description:
An outstanding conversion, well-located with so many possibilities!
Formerly a saw factory, this spacious building has been meticulously converted by its designer and engineer owners into a light-filled residence with superbly versatile work-from-home spaces. Zoned Commercial 2 in a street-art precinct close to Smith Street cafes and the Convent arts park, this striking home incorporates a large office adjoining a vast workshop with northern light and potential use as a gallery or architects' studio. Brilliantly designed living spaces include an expansive upper-level living and dining room with soaring gabled ceiling, open to a Smeg-equipped kitchen (stainless steel benchtops, timber cabinetry) and opening to a walkway and sunny al fresco entertaining deck; two double bedrooms (BIRs, elegant ensuite to main) plus fitted study; stylish second bathroom and euro laundry. Including 2-car ROW access parking, this unique property features polished concrete and timber floors, hydronic heating, split-system air conditioning and security entrance.

Captivating Victorian Seeks Your Inspiration (STCA)
Positioned in a quiet one-way street, a heartbeat away from trendy Smith Street cafes establishes an irresistible context for this charming Victorian cottage, which presents remarkable scope for a renovation (Heritage Overlay, STCA.) Beyond a picturesque profile, beautiful period traits such as Baltic timber floors and soaring decorative ceilings instantly captivate, while Collingwood train station, trams, the CBD, Gertrude and Victoria Street are just steps away!
- Two bedrooms branch off the romantic classic hallway and feature high intricate ceilings
- Central bathroom with integrated laundry is ripe for a splash of contemporary delight (STCA)
- Welcoming lounge room with an open fireplace sets the scene for relaxation
- Well-equipped kitchen features every necessity for the home chef including a dishwasher
- Sun-filled paved courtyard is an excellent area for alfresco dining & requires no upkeep
- Rear access to Sturt Street, split system heating/air conditioning and rich period attributes
Conditions of entry - IDENTIFICATION and contact number required, otherwise entry may be refused.

Description:
'A house in the sky': magnificent penthouse with panoramic views
One of a kind! This outstandingly spacious and quiet penthouse apartment set over two levels (approx. 250m2 total area) with sweeping north/south views from soaring glass walls is the ultimate city-edge residence. Moments from East Melbourne parks and all the lifestyle attractions of Fitzroy and Collingwood, this luxurious home is distinguished by large light-flooded rooms, a vast roof garden for al fresco entertaining, a spectacular 'Winter Garden' atrium terrace, and balconies opening from a fitted study and two of its three large bedrooms. A versatile floor plan incorporates a spacious living room opening to the terrace; a grandly proportioned living/dining room open to a bespoke kitchen (Asko appliances and pantry); home office; two stunning bathrooms, powder room and euro laundry. Including lift entry, two secure car spaces and storage cage, this brilliant property, designed for long-term family living, features generous custom storage, double glazing, superior appointments, brush box floors, split-system air conditioning and video intercom.

Description:
Two Bedroom Design Elegance at ?The Stanley?.
The heritage facade of Collingwood?s acclaimed Foy & Gibson redevelopment, belies a contemporary makeover encapsulating the best of urban living. Level one of ?The Stanley?, this near new apartment borrows its design from a classic Scandinavian aesthetic, with light timber floorboards, clean white walls and neutral contrast tiling. Featuring a custom all-white Nordic chic kitchen with stone benches, island bench/breakfast bar, quality stainless steel appliances and masses of storage, a practically appointed laundry area and generous sun-washed living zone extending out to a large covered entertainers terrace balcony. Two generously proportioned and carpeted bedrooms, awash with natural light, each include BIR?s, the master providing stylish en-suite and built-in study area. An additional luxury bathroom showcases attractive feature tiling, large walk-in shower and concealed cistern. The property boasts central heating and air-conditioning, double glazed windows, secure parking and a substantial storage cage. Located above a supermarket, ?The Stanley? also includes three private courtyard gardens, two rooftop BBQ entertaining terraces and library/lounge. Ideally situated in close proximity to public transport, shops, cafes, bars and restaurants, with easy access to the CBD, this special apartment makes a winning lifestyle decision or informed investment decision.

Description:
Enormous entertaining terrace!
Stunning style starts when you step foot into one of the area's most impressive developments and culminates in this captivating contemporary apartment with amazing city views. With popular Smith Street's endless array of retail and culinary options all within a few metres, you'll be spoiled for choice in this exceptional inner-city location. This single-level apartment offers stylish space, loads of light and superb elevated views. Features 2 bedrooms with built-in robes, well equipped kitchen with high quality appliances and stone benches, sophisticated open-plan living and dining area overlooking an enormous entertainment terrace. Features include dual heating/cooling, video intercom, polished hardwood floors, secure lift access, communal gardens/ entertaining areas and basement car space. (CURRENTLY RETURNING $65,000 PER ANNUM approx).

Description:
Sensational Starter or Blue Chip Investment
One of only twelve in a secure refurbished block, this second-floor corner abode is perfectly positioned to take advantage of every lifestyle Collingwood has to offer. Bathed in natural light, this North Facing apartment's pristine interior comprises two double bedrooms (both with robes), stylish bathroom and separate WC, open lounge/dining area with city skyline views additionally a lock-up garage via gated driveway. An updated kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances, built-in breakfast bar, internal laundry facilities and intercom/secure entry foyer. Easy access to Smith Street cafes and trams, renowned restaurants and shopping precincts as well as Johnston Street buses and Victoria Park Station.

Description:
Historic "Foy & Gibson" Apartment with Panoramic Views
Perched at the top of a historic "Foy and Gibson" brick warehouse is this unique and spacious contemporary apartment featuring spectacular views that extend 270 degrees from the Melbourne CBD through to the Dandenong Ranges. Framed by polished timber floors, whitewashed walls and high ceilings, this split-level apartment comprises an entrance hall, two good sized bedrooms, master with walk in robes, a spacious and private balcony and ensuite bathroom. On the top level you will marvel at the panoramic views from either of the two large entertaining balconies and the substantial living and dining spaces bathed in natural light. The sleek, streamlined kitchen features stone benchtops and stainless steel European appliances. The dining area boasts a built in entertainment unit with storage cupboards designed to conceal a potential bar fridge and further appliances. The top level also includes a small study nook and second bathroom. This brilliant apartment includes heating, air conditioning and an enormous secure two or three car garage with remote roller door access from within the secure basement car park. Located just moments away from cosmopolitan Smith, Gertrude and Brunswick Streets that provide residents with the best of inner city living lifestyle with public transport, cafes, restaurants and bars all at your fingertips.

Description:
FLAWLESSLY RENOVATED WITH A WAREHOUSE CONVERSION TWIST
Captivating sun drenched apartment with customised high-end features and stunning views.
- 2 large bedrooms featuring custom built-in robes, 100% wool carpet, Nobo heaters
- Beautifully renovated kitchen with Messmate hardwood benchtops, Bosch appliances, USB power
- Living and dining complimented perfectly with polished concrete floors, built-in hardwood shelving, premium Daikin split system
- Immaculately renovated bathroom with Methven tapware, heated towel rail, European laundry
- Enjoy city views from a private balcony streaming off the living area
- Secure gated parking and additional parking permits for guests
- In a block of only 11, with new windows and doors throughout
Be quick to secure your slice of bustling Collingwood! This brilliant inner city locale is walking distance to Johnston and Smith Street's fabulous cafes, restaurants, and shops - as well as trains, buses, trams, the Yarra River bike trails, and much much more.
